name: sirohydrochlorin cobaltochelatase
classes: Sole sub-subclass for lyases that do not belong in the other subclasses
comment: This enzyme is a type II chelatase, being either a monomer (CbiX) or a homodimer (CibK) and being ATP-independent. CbiK from Salmonella enterica uses precorrin-2 as the substrate to yield cobalt-precorrin-2. The enzyme contains two histidines at the active site that are thought to be involved in the deprotonation of the tetrapyrrole substrate as well as in metal binding. CbiX from Bacillus megaterium inserts cobalt at the level of sirohydrochlorin (factor-II) rather than precorrin-2.

references.title: Common chelatase design in the branched tetrapyrrole pathways of heme and anaerobic cobalamin synthesis.
A story of chelatase evolution: identification and characterization of a small 13-15-kDa "ancestral" cobaltochelatase (CbiXS) in the archaea.
